STATE of North Carolina
v.
Kenneth Wayne WILLIAMS. No. 105P06. Supreme Court of North Carolina. April 6, 2006. Kenneth W. Williams, Pro Se. Scott T. Stroud, Assistant Attorney General, Howard S. Boney, Jr., District Attorney, for State of NC.

ORDER

Upon consideration of the petition filed on the 1st day of March 2006 by Defendant in this matter for discretionary review of the decision of the North Carolina Court of Appeals pursuant to G.S. 7A-31, the following order was entered and is hereby certified to the North Carolina Court of Appeals:

"Dismissed by order of the Court in conference, this the 6th day of April 2006."
